1
00:00:01,630 --> 00:00:02,370
Zen...

2
00:00:06,410 --> 00:00:07,470
I like you.

3
00:00:11,710 --> 00:00:12,420
Me too.

4
00:00:14,900 --> 00:00:15,760
I only want you.

5
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:18,710
No one else will do.

6
00:00:20,530 --> 00:00:21,160
Sorry.

7
00:00:22,210 --> 00:00:23,010
I'm afraid...

8
00:00:25,180 --> 00:00:26,640
I can't hold back anymore.

9
00:01:16,250 --> 00:01:17,450
How should I put it?

10
00:01:20,289 --> 00:01:22,550
I think I dreamed of things from the past.

11
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,270
Yeah.

12
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:30,650
We've grown up.

13
00:01:32,580 --> 00:01:33,630
What?

14
00:01:38,979 --> 00:01:40,020
I...

15
00:01:41,289 --> 00:01:41,830
Yeah.

16
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:45,960
I felt a little scared last night

17
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,920
when I was sleeping.

18
00:01:51,229 --> 00:01:52,100
Scared of what?

19
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:57,570
Scared that being lovers with you

20
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:00,270
is nothing but a dream.

21
00:02:02,950 --> 00:02:05,210
Scared that when I wake up in the morning,

22
00:02:07,870 --> 00:02:10,699
you're not in my arms.

23
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,260
Don't be silly,

24
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:26,200
you idiot.

25
00:02:37,930 --> 00:02:39,090
Honestly,

26
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:47,290
I might never be able
to let you go in this life.

27
00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:51,100
Well, I guess I have no choice then.

28
00:02:51,710 --> 00:02:53,770
Let me make you happy.

29
00:02:57,680 --> 00:03:00,080
I really have good taste
in choosing my man.

30
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:02,650
Me too.

31
00:03:35,390 --> 00:03:36,240
Good morning.

32
00:03:40,570 --> 00:03:42,010
Good morning.

33
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,910
No matter how you look at it,
I'm the winner.

34
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:49,079
You're only winning on KPI.

35
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:51,180
I'm the real winner
when it comes to profits.

36
00:03:51,180 --> 00:03:54,640
You just pulled off
another standard big event.

37
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:57,780
The clients I brought in are all new.

38
00:03:57,810 --> 00:04:00,830
You don't get it. We got twice
as many clients as last year.

39
00:04:00,830 --> 00:04:03,440
You just hired a famous band
to attract clients.

40
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,460
That wasn't exactly hard, was it?

41
00:04:04,460 --> 00:04:06,230
Well, you two, that's enough.

42
00:04:06,550 --> 00:04:07,650
-Ah?
-Ah?

43
00:04:08,350 --> 00:04:10,220
I'm sorry.

44
00:04:11,270 --> 00:04:13,180
I don't think
someone with social anxiety like you

45
00:04:13,180 --> 00:04:15,840
can earn the artists' trust.

46
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:18,190
Hah, I've been doing it easily
the whole time.

47
00:04:18,190 --> 00:04:19,380
And hey,

48
00:04:19,410 --> 00:04:21,649
you just took back first place.

49
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:23,610
Is it really okay for you to get so cocky?

50
00:04:23,610 --> 00:04:25,510
Huh?

51
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:28,940
We've been competing by KPI
from the very beginning, so I win.

52
00:04:29,030 --> 00:04:29,760
That's it.

53
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,310
I don't accept it.

54
00:04:35,220 --> 00:04:36,350
Impressive, right?

55
00:04:36,430 --> 00:04:38,200
Yeah, really impressive.

56
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:41,590
As soon as Mr. Yotsuya came back
from his business trip,

57
00:04:41,590 --> 00:04:43,650
he suddenly started acting that way.

58
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,800
Gosh.

59
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:47,190
It was like a fight between kids.

60
00:04:47,210 --> 00:04:48,150
Yeah.

61
00:04:48,170 --> 00:04:50,530
Normally both of them are so capable.

62
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,560
I have to go.

63
00:05:08,870 --> 00:05:10,430
One more minute.

64
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:14,240
That's enough.

65
00:05:14,570 --> 00:05:16,550
-It hurts.
-I've told you many times.

66
00:05:16,550 --> 00:05:18,810
Focus on work while we're at the company.

67
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:21,950
You were gone on that trip for so long.
I finally get to see you.

68
00:05:21,950 --> 00:05:23,090
It won't hurt to stay a little longer.

69
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:25,090
This has nothing to do with the trip.

70
00:05:25,150 --> 00:05:27,480
I've told you
it's not okay at the company.

71
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:34,760
I've also told you

72
00:05:36,210 --> 00:05:37,409
that if this keeps up,

73
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:40,770
I won't be able to get any work done.

74
00:05:43,670 --> 00:05:44,480
Well,

75
00:05:45,260 --> 00:05:46,610
we can continue the rest at home today.

76
00:05:46,610 --> 00:05:48,610
It's your fault. I won't do it today.

77
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:54,550
Just kidding.

78
00:05:54,570 --> 00:05:56,900
Don't complain even if it's late.

79
00:07:01,350 --> 00:07:05,240
[Fake Fact Lips]

80
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:10,570
[Episode 6
The Word "Practically" Is Unnecessary]

81
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:09,840
Mr. Yotsuya,

82
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:11,620
I've finally found you.

83
00:07:11,650 --> 00:07:12,460
I'm sorry.

84
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:15,790
Just now, Senshin Publishing sent over
the production schedule.

85
00:07:15,790 --> 00:07:18,890
It's a bit different from what we made.

86
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:21,780
Ah, they sent an email
saying there were changes.

87
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:23,460
-Isn't that it?
-Ah.

88
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,330
I'll check it again.

89
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:26,770
Yotsuya.

90
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:29,830
-Yes.
-We need you at the evening meeting.

91
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,140
Well...

92
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,620
It's at 5 PM, right?

93
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,400
Would it be okay

94
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:37,720
if I arrive a little late?

95
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:40,040
No problem at all. Thank you.

96
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:43,040
Mr. Yotsuya, I'm sorry.

97
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:45,180
-I got that email.
-See?

98
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:45,909
Mr. Yotsuya.

99
00:07:45,909 --> 00:07:48,080
The client wants more options
for the brand accent colors.

100
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:49,770
Ah, I knew it.

101
00:07:50,250 --> 00:07:53,750
I figured this might happen,
so I prepared a list in advance.

102
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:55,470
Tell them I can send it over
by the end of today.

103
00:07:55,470 --> 00:07:57,070
Got it. I'll pass that along.

104
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:58,900
Oh, right.

105
00:07:59,060 --> 00:07:59,840
Tonight,

106
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:02,750
Mr. Saeki from Gaisei Shoji invited me out
for drinks tonight.

107
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,450
Can you come with me?

108
00:08:04,470 --> 00:08:06,320
Mr. Saeki?

109
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:09,380
Yes. He asked me
to bring you along, Mr. Yotsuya.

110
00:08:09,910 --> 00:08:11,290
I'm not going.

111
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:12,130
Eh?

112
00:08:12,150 --> 00:08:12,970
Because...

113
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,250
if I get stuck with him,
I'll end up drinking till dawn.

114
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:17,180
That's why I don't want to go alone.

115
00:08:17,210 --> 00:08:19,330
If it's just about drinking,
it doesn't have to be me, right?

116
00:08:19,330 --> 00:08:20,790
Look. What about that guy?

117
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,540
You two started here around the same time,
didn't you?

118
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:23,920
No, I'm not going.

119
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:25,070
Why?

120
00:08:25,090 --> 00:08:27,120
Because there's a game
I want to play right away at home.

121
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,880
How heartless.

122
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:30,610
Please don't leave me alone.

123
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,679
He's your client.

124
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:34,070
I'll make it up to you.

125
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:34,990
No.

126
00:08:35,010 --> 00:08:36,470
Why?

127
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,690
Someone's waiting for me at home.

128
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,490
Someone at home?

129
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:46,760
Eh?

130
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:48,730
Mr. Yotsuya, you're in a relationship?

131
00:08:48,730 --> 00:08:50,200
Tell us more.

132
00:08:50,220 --> 00:08:52,210
Why are you always so nosy?

133
00:08:52,230 --> 00:08:52,790
Go away.

134
00:08:52,810 --> 00:08:53,740
How long has this been going on?

135
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:54,840
Where did you two meet?

136
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,790
What kind of person is she?

137
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:56,970
Is she from our company?

138
00:08:56,970 --> 00:08:57,810
From the Secretarial Section?

139
00:08:57,810 --> 00:08:58,520
From the General Affairs Section?

140
00:08:58,520 --> 00:08:59,590
From another company?

141
00:08:59,590 --> 00:09:01,370
Is she older or younger than you?

142
00:09:01,370 --> 00:09:02,230
What type of person is she?

143
00:09:02,230 --> 00:09:04,300
You're so annoying!

144
00:09:14,330 --> 00:09:15,680
Respectable

145
00:09:16,370 --> 00:09:17,920
and cute.

146
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:23,420
-Ah!
-Ah!

147
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,030
-Ah!
-Ah!

148
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:28,210
-Wow!
-Wow!

149
00:09:30,490 --> 00:09:31,530
You...

150
00:09:32,690 --> 00:09:35,060
Don't say weird things at work.

151
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,510
It's no big deal.

152
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:40,140
I just said that I'm in a relationship.

153
00:09:40,170 --> 00:09:41,250
That's true.

154
00:09:43,370 --> 00:09:46,370
No one would ever guess
I'm in a relationship with you.

155
00:09:47,710 --> 00:09:48,580
Hey.

156
00:09:48,990 --> 00:09:50,590
Wait until I finish my drink.

157
00:09:53,370 --> 00:09:54,420
Stop it.

158
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:55,280
Give it back.

159
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:02,090
I've been holding back the whole time.

160
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:04,290
Then you should have held back
at the company.

161
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:06,220
Fine, I'll admit that was my fault.

162
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:09,360
I haven't seen your face for so long,
so I feel...

163
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,060
Don't make excuses.

164
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:15,070
I'm sorry.

165
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:17,860
I'll be more careful.

166
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:26,920
If I can't focus on work because of you,

167
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:31,320
then the time we get to spend together
will be less, right?

168
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,280
You're also…

169
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:40,050
trying to make time for us?

170
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:41,950
Of course.

171
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:44,580
I also feel bad that I'm always so busy.

172
00:10:45,950 --> 00:10:48,880
After all,
we're practically in a relationship now.

173
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,980
The word "practically" is unnecessary.

174
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,560
I can't hold back much longer.

175
00:11:09,330 --> 00:11:11,440
Let me take my time with this drink.

176
00:11:11,470 --> 00:11:13,090
If I let you take your time,

177
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,300
later you'll just

178
00:11:14,330 --> 00:11:15,240
fall asleep.

179
00:11:16,970 --> 00:11:17,790
Mm.

180
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:19,580
Well then,

181
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,650
-it all depends on how you do.
-Huh?

182
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,010
Really?

183
00:11:26,130 --> 00:11:26,830
Mm?

184
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:29,800
I'll do my best!

185
00:11:29,830 --> 00:11:30,680
Hurry up and drink.

186
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:32,180
Okay, okay. Calm down.

187
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,020
Are you good now?

188
00:11:33,020 --> 00:11:33,430
Yeah.

189
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:35,530
I'll do my best!

190
00:11:35,550 --> 00:11:38,420
I know you'll do your best.
Put on your clothes first.

191
00:11:38,420 --> 00:11:39,940
I'll take them off anyway.

192
00:11:39,970 --> 00:11:40,660
Stand up.

193
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:42,580
Ugh, fine, I got it.

194
00:11:42,610 --> 00:11:42,890
Okay.

195
00:11:42,890 --> 00:11:43,420
And then?

196
00:11:44,690 --> 00:11:45,400
Let's go.

197
00:11:45,890 --> 00:11:46,830
Gosh.

198
00:11:46,860 --> 00:11:48,720
Don't say that.

199
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:24,900
Are you awake?

200
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,460
Barely awake.

201
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:43,070
In this quarter,

202
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,230
you won, didn't you?

203
00:12:47,970 --> 00:12:48,760
Yeah.

204
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:52,670
Is there anything you want me to do?

205
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:54,260
Eh?

206
00:12:56,570 --> 00:12:58,050
Not really.

207
00:12:59,930 --> 00:13:01,050
Come on.

208
00:13:01,850 --> 00:13:03,250
That's so boring.

209
00:13:04,370 --> 00:13:08,380
Competing against someone like you
who doesn't even get upset when they lose

210
00:13:08,380 --> 00:13:09,780
is what's really boring.

211
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:13,150
After all,

212
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:16,740
you were the one who came up with the rule
in the first place.

213
00:13:17,050 --> 00:13:19,910
I don't have anything in particular
I want you to do.

214
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,080
Alright, alright.

215
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,100
No matter what the result is,

216
00:13:26,970 --> 00:13:28,980
it's a reward for you, right?

217
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:31,790
Yeah, that's true.

218
00:13:32,890 --> 00:13:34,420
You know me so well.

219
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:37,480
Ah.

220
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:38,830
But

221
00:13:39,070 --> 00:13:40,670
if I have to say something...

222
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:41,840
Mm?

223
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:48,000
I want to know more about you.

224
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:49,890
Eh?

225
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:53,040
You know so much about me,

226
00:13:54,150 --> 00:13:55,160
yet about you...

227
00:13:55,380 --> 00:13:58,710
For example, I don't know anything
about your college days.

228
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:01,350
That's because

229
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:03,930
you didn't ask me anything.

230
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:05,090
Also,

231
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,710
I'm bothered
that you said you like sleeping with guys.

232
00:14:07,710 --> 00:14:09,930
No, that was just a lie. I was bragging.

233
00:14:09,950 --> 00:14:11,680
That still sounds suspicious.

234
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:13,280
Forget it.

235
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:16,300
I'm not trying to rake up the past.

236
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:19,990
But this rule benefits you too much.
It's unfair.

237
00:14:22,630 --> 00:14:23,890
Because

238
00:14:25,970 --> 00:14:28,500
there are so many things
I want you to do for me.

239
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:33,570
But if I don't ask you like this,
you'll never do them. What else can I do?

240
00:14:33,570 --> 00:14:35,470
What else do you want me to do?

241
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:42,560
Tell me ten things you like about me.

242
00:14:43,110 --> 00:14:44,700
How can I possibly come up with that?

243
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:45,380
See?

244
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:47,140
It only benefits you.

245
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:48,000
Well,

246
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,840
just say something
that puts me on the spot.

247
00:14:52,140 --> 00:14:52,690
Ah.

248
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:55,250
-What's wrong?
-Nothing.

249
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,900
I just remembered something
completely irrelevant.

250
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:58,760
What?

251
00:15:01,780 --> 00:15:02,720
What is this?

252
00:15:09,270 --> 00:15:12,090
[RID RANDAL Ticket]

253
00:15:10,490 --> 00:15:11,780
RID RANDAL!

254
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:13,630
How did you get it?

255
00:15:13,630 --> 00:15:15,970
From an event company I worked with.

256
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:16,830
Do you want to go with me?

257
00:15:16,830 --> 00:15:17,910
Well, I...

258
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,010
Did I tell you I like RID RANDAL?

259
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:20,800
Did you?

260
00:15:20,930 --> 00:15:22,190
So it's a coincidence?

261
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:22,460
Yes.

262
00:15:22,470 --> 00:15:23,280
Really?

263
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:26,090
I've liked them since college.

264
00:15:26,110 --> 00:15:27,040
Oh, I see.

265
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:29,900
Yeah.
They've become really popular recently.

266
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:32,820
I also entered the lottery for the concert,
but I didn't win. Not long ago,

267
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:34,240
I didn't get selected
the second time either.

268
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:36,560
I'd already given up,
but you managed to get the tickets.

269
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,470
They said it's a thank-you gift
for handling some troublesome work.

270
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:39,680
Really?

271
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:41,330
Wow, amazing.

272
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:43,610
It's been so long
since I last listened to their music.

273
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:44,570
We...

274
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:46,580
-It'll be our first proper date, right?
-Yes.

275
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:47,400
If we go to the concert,

276
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,940
I'll be over the moon.

277
00:15:48,970 --> 00:15:50,970
RID RANDAL is so amazing.

278
00:15:50,990 --> 00:15:54,120
We also invited RID RANDAL
to the previous event,

279
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:55,900
but their schedule was completely packed.

280
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:57,850
They're absolutely the most popular.

281
00:15:57,850 --> 00:15:58,970
Their songs also have dominated

282
00:15:58,970 --> 00:16:02,200
the karaoke charts these days.

283
00:16:02,910 --> 00:16:04,200
It's all RID RANDAL.

284
00:16:04,220 --> 00:16:05,570
Yeah, okay.

285
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,290
I can share it soon.

286
00:16:07,310 --> 00:16:08,070
Okay.

287
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:11,180
Okay. Perfect, the documents just came in.

288
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:13,070
Okay. I'll send it over. Okay, I'm sorry.

289
00:16:13,070 --> 00:16:14,110
Thank you for your help.

290
00:16:14,110 --> 00:16:14,730
Thank you.

291
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:15,650
Oh, right.

292
00:16:15,670 --> 00:16:17,010
How much of the proposal have you done?

293
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:20,080
Ah... Well, about 80 percent left.

294
00:16:20,110 --> 00:16:21,420
Eh? You've only done 20 percent?

295
00:16:21,420 --> 00:16:23,970
Ah, I misspoke.
I've done about 80 percent already.

296
00:16:23,970 --> 00:16:25,130
About 20 percent left.

297
00:16:25,130 --> 00:16:26,190
Okay. Show it to me when you're done.

298
00:16:26,190 --> 00:16:26,590
Got it.

299
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,080
I'll finish it right away.

300
00:16:28,110 --> 00:16:29,170
No rush. It's fine.

301
00:16:29,190 --> 00:16:29,840
Okay.

302
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:44,560
[RID RANDAL Ticket]

303
00:16:43,830 --> 00:16:45,430
Do you have any plans later?

304
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:48,010
Not really.

305
00:16:52,030 --> 00:16:53,090
Is it a date?

306
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:55,170
Eh?

307
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:58,420
Mr. Yotsuya is in a relationship.
And Mr. Shido, you too?

308
00:16:58,430 --> 00:16:59,670
So what if it is?

309
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:01,520
-Eh?
-Eh?

310
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:03,280
Mr. Shido.

311
00:17:03,310 --> 00:17:06,030
Do you two even compete
over who has a girlfriend?

312
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:07,220
Who would do that?

313
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:09,400
But the timing is way too coincidental.

314
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,660
It's just a coincidence.

315
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:13,750
You're clearly busier than us.
How did you find a girlfriend?

316
00:17:13,750 --> 00:17:15,140
Please teach me.

317
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,460
Don't you already have a girlfriend?

318
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:20,869
We broke up.

319
00:17:21,170 --> 00:17:22,650
Really?

320
00:17:22,670 --> 00:17:24,480
Weren't you together
for about 3 years?

321
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,680
Yeah. We started dating back in school.

322
00:17:27,970 --> 00:17:30,050
I've been too busy with work lately.

323
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:32,100
It's crazy

324
00:17:32,130 --> 00:17:33,870
how feelings can just fade in an instant.

325
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:36,850
I hate to admit it,
but that's pretty common.

326
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:37,550
Yes.

327
00:17:39,090 --> 00:17:41,000
You should be careful too, Mr. Shido.

328
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,540
The time you get to spend together
is very precious.

329
00:17:43,540 --> 00:17:44,680
I know that.

330
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:47,410
Oh, right, Higashino.

331
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,130
Though there's no rush,

332
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:50,370
don't slack off on your work.

333
00:17:50,370 --> 00:17:51,600
Okay, I'm sorry.

334
00:17:51,980 --> 00:17:53,570
Exactly, Higashino.

335
00:17:53,590 --> 00:17:55,090
No rush, but keep things moving.

336
00:17:55,090 --> 00:17:55,650
Okay.

337
00:17:57,050 --> 00:17:57,800
What?

338
00:17:59,230 --> 00:17:59,750
Okay.

339
00:18:11,210 --> 00:18:13,360
All right, it's done.

340
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:15,260
Mr. Shido.

341
00:18:15,290 --> 00:18:15,740
Yeah.

342
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:17,760
Could you please check it?

343
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:18,500
Ah.

344
00:18:23,380 --> 00:18:24,000
Mm.

345
00:18:24,510 --> 00:18:26,000
Just swap this and this.

346
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:27,440
Got it.

347
00:18:27,470 --> 00:18:28,260
Thank you.

348
00:18:28,540 --> 00:18:29,580
Then I'll head off now.

349
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:30,910
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

350
00:18:37,130 --> 00:18:38,460
Hello, this is Shido.

351
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:42,060
Ah, thank you for the other day.

352
00:18:42,460 --> 00:18:43,210
Yes.

353
00:18:46,180 --> 00:18:46,670
Okay.

354
00:18:49,510 --> 00:18:50,230
I see.

355
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:02,980
[RID RANDAL Poster]

356
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,810
[RID RANDAL Poster]

357
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,180
[Got called away by a client]

358
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:16,540
[Probably won't be able to get there
until after the show]

359
00:19:16,570 --> 00:19:18,170
[Sorry]

360
00:19:26,990 --> 00:19:28,080
Mr. Yotsuya.

361
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:53,590
Oh, Shido.

362
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:54,760
Oh.

363
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,320
You're here.

364
00:19:56,340 --> 00:19:57,360
Sorry, I didn't make it in time.

365
00:19:57,360 --> 00:19:58,770
It's okay.

366
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,200
Don't worry about it.

367
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,020
By the way...

368
00:20:02,260 --> 00:20:03,360
Oh, right.

369
00:20:04,230 --> 00:20:06,090
I ran into Miss Kiritani
and Ms. Matsushita by chance.

370
00:20:06,090 --> 00:20:07,050
Yes.

371
00:20:07,070 --> 00:20:09,450
We ran into each other at the entrance.
I was so surprised.

372
00:20:09,450 --> 00:20:11,070
I see.

373
00:20:11,090 --> 00:20:11,960
Long time no see.

374
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:12,990
Long time no see.

375
00:20:13,020 --> 00:20:14,110
Long time no see.

376
00:20:14,830 --> 00:20:15,540
Huh?

377
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:18,940
Could it be Mr. Shido?

378
00:20:19,130 --> 00:20:20,410
What do you mean?

379
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:23,950
The one
Mr. Yotsuya said couldn't make it today.

380
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:27,090
I thought it was his girlfriend.

381
00:20:27,110 --> 00:20:28,830
It's nothing like that.

382
00:20:28,850 --> 00:20:30,920
I really wish
Mr. Shido could have heard it too.

383
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,880
The way the fourth song kicked in...

384
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:34,340
That was amazing, wasn't it?

385
00:20:34,340 --> 00:20:35,060
Really amazing.

386
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:35,650
Right?

387
00:20:35,670 --> 00:20:37,010
Isn't that in the album?

388
00:20:37,030 --> 00:20:37,610
Yes.

389
00:20:37,630 --> 00:20:38,630
The way it kicked in
was completely different, right?

390
00:20:38,630 --> 00:20:39,360
Totally different.

391
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:40,220
The arrangement was amazing.

392
00:20:40,220 --> 00:20:40,690
Amazing.

393
00:20:40,690 --> 00:20:41,740
Really amazing.

394
00:20:41,770 --> 00:20:42,810
You noticed that too?

395
00:20:42,810 --> 00:20:43,590
Well...

396
00:20:43,620 --> 00:20:44,410
Do you

397
00:20:44,430 --> 00:20:46,270
like them too, Mr. Shido?

398
00:20:47,770 --> 00:20:49,410
Eh? Ah.

399
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:51,640
No, I don't really know much about them.

400
00:20:51,740 --> 00:20:53,700
It's just that Yotsuya
has liked them for a long time.

401
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:55,170
I see.

402
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,800
Matsushita is also a big fan.

403
00:20:56,830 --> 00:20:57,850
She and Mr. Yotsuya

404
00:20:57,850 --> 00:20:59,350
have a lot to talk about.

405
00:20:59,380 --> 00:21:01,840
Both of them know more than I do.

406
00:21:01,860 --> 00:21:02,770
I see.

407
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:05,060
It's the first time
I've had a proper chat

408
00:21:05,060 --> 00:21:07,320
with Mr. Yotsuya.

409
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,230
He's really

410
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,780
a very interesting person.

411
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,150
He didn't say anything rude, did he?

412
00:21:12,170 --> 00:21:13,720
No, not at all.

413
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:16,360
He said you were the one
who gave him the ticket, Mr. Shido.

414
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:17,890
He seemed really grateful.

415
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:19,350
Is that so?

416
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:21,000
Since we're all here,

417
00:21:21,220 --> 00:21:23,080
let's go for a drink later.

418
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:24,590
Oh, sure.

419
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:28,720
What do you think?

420
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:31,270
Well...

421
00:21:31,910 --> 00:21:33,240
Yes, but...

422
00:21:33,740 --> 00:21:35,230
Ah, sorry.

423
00:21:35,260 --> 00:21:36,520
It's okay. It's totally fine.

424
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:37,480
But...

425
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:39,510
let's do it another time.

426
00:21:39,530 --> 00:21:40,270
Okay, sounds good.

427
00:21:40,270 --> 00:21:40,800
Yeah.

428
00:21:40,820 --> 00:21:42,840
Mr. Shido, let's hang out together
next time.

429
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:45,360
Okay. I'll do some research by then.

430
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,070
Okay, then.

431
00:21:47,090 --> 00:21:48,490
We're heading off now.

432
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:49,020
See you next time.

433
00:21:49,020 --> 00:21:49,570
Okay.

434
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,330
Ms. Matsushita,
who was with Miss Kiritani,

435
00:21:55,330 --> 00:21:56,830
is super funny.

436
00:21:56,850 --> 00:21:58,960
When the most upbeat song came on
during the concert,

437
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,190
she suddenly started headbanging.

438
00:22:00,190 --> 00:22:03,480
I said it wasn't that kind of song,

439
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:05,210
and even Miss Kiritani was stunned.

440
00:22:05,210 --> 00:22:08,510
The look on her face
was just way too funny.

441
00:22:12,120 --> 00:22:12,870
Zen.

442
00:22:14,970 --> 00:22:16,300
Hey, Zen.

443
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,430
What's wrong? Are you angry?

444
00:22:19,430 --> 00:22:20,250
I'm not angry.

445
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:21,530
You're clearly angry.

446
00:22:22,380 --> 00:22:23,420
Why?

447
00:22:25,850 --> 00:22:27,760
Eh? Are you jealous?

448
00:22:28,270 --> 00:22:30,140
Huh? No way.

449
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:31,090
You totally are.

450
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:33,520
Is it because I had a good time

451
00:22:33,540 --> 00:22:35,540
talking with them?

452
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:36,720
What do you mean?

453
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:38,990
Nothing. To be honest,

454
00:22:40,220 --> 00:22:42,150
I didn't expect you to get jealous.

455
00:22:43,090 --> 00:22:45,490
Guess I'm just a petty man.

456
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:47,080
I'm heading home.

457
00:22:47,690 --> 00:22:49,390
It's my fault.

458
00:22:49,650 --> 00:22:51,010
I'm not mad at you.

459
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:51,770
Eh?

460
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:53,520
I...

461
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:57,040
I didn't even know
what kind of music you like.

462
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:59,390
It's no big deal.

463
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:00,470
I...

464
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:05,290
I thought I'd be fine
no matter who you got along with.

465
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:08,710
You're friendly to everyone.

466
00:23:10,150 --> 00:23:11,750
You really know how to win people over.

467
00:23:11,750 --> 00:23:13,630
See? You are really mad at me.

468
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:14,500
No.

469
00:23:14,520 --> 00:23:15,790
I just think...

470
00:23:16,890 --> 00:23:19,330
it's embarrassing that I still get jealous
over something so small

471
00:23:19,330 --> 00:23:22,140
and can't even control my own emotions.

472
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:28,380
Let's just call it a day.

473
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:30,980
I'll calm down after a while.

474
00:23:33,380 --> 00:23:35,360
How can I possibly leave you alone?

475
00:24:00,740 --> 00:24:03,530
[Development]

476
00:24:06,830 --> 00:24:07,630
Good morning.

477
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:21,630
Hey, Shido.

478
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,660
Long time no see.

479
00:24:24,970 --> 00:24:26,170
Futami.

480
00:24:29,290 --> 00:24:30,200
Futami?

481
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,540
You...

482
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:53,840
[In the Next Episode]

483
00:25:51,660 --> 00:25:52,970
Looking forward to working with you.

484
00:25:52,970 --> 00:25:55,320
Futami's transfer is so sudden.

485
00:25:53,860 --> 00:25:57,020
[Episode 7 I'm Joining This Battle Too]

486
00:25:55,340 --> 00:25:57,250
If that guy comes,

487
00:25:57,270 --> 00:25:59,270
things are going to get interesting.

488
00:25:59,270 --> 00:26:01,460
Hey, Shido.

489
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:03,240
Looking forward to working with you again.

490
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:04,700
Yeah, same here.

491
00:26:04,720 --> 00:26:06,360
Are you two in touch with each other?

492
00:26:06,360 --> 00:26:08,090
They're still as close as ever.

493
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:09,980
They even went on a trip together.

494
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:11,080
A trip?

495
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:12,690
Let's grab a drink, just the two of us.

496
00:26:12,690 --> 00:26:14,600
Why do you want to compete with us
so badly?

497
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:18,020
Because I'm a better match for Yotsuya
than you are.

498
00:26:18,050 --> 00:26:19,610
I'm staying over tonight.
